---
import FridayHarborLayout from '../../layouts/FridayHarborLayout.astro';
import { entries } from '../../data/friday-harbor';
const entry = entries.find(e => e.slug === '2026-04-25-eye-of-the-needle')!;
---
<FridayHarborLayout entry={entry}>
  <figure slot="figure" class="hormuz-figure">
    <div class="hormuz-stage" id="stage" aria-label="Map of the Strait of Hormuz">
      <p class="map-status">
        <span data-lang="en">Loading map...</span>
        <span data-lang="zh">地图加载中...</span>
      </p>
    </div>
    <figcaption data-lang="en">
      <b>How a 39-km strait edits the world's oil.</b>
      Iran on the north shore, Oman's Musandam exclave on the south.
      Every commercial tanker bound for the Indian Ocean threads the same dotted lane.
      &nbsp;<b class="event-mark">①</b> M/V Ararat (24 Apr) &nbsp;
      <b class="event-mark">②</b> M/V Heron Star (25 Apr) — both seized within visual range of the Iranian-held islands of Qeshm, Larak, and Hormuz.
    </figcaption>
    <figcaption data-lang="zh">
      <b>一条 39 公里的海峡，如何改写世界石油的命运。</b>
      北岸是伊朗，南岸是阿曼飞地穆桑代姆半岛。
      所有驶向印度洋的商船都顺着同一条虚线航道穿出。
      &nbsp;<b class="event-mark">①</b> 阿拉拉特号（4 月 24 日） &nbsp;
      <b class="event-mark">②</b> 苍鹭星号（4 月 25 日）—— 两次扣船均发生在伊朗管辖的格什姆、拉腊克、霍尔木兹三岛视野之内。
    </figcaption>
  </figure>

  <div slot="notebook-en">
    <p>
      Most of the world's oil that travels by sea travels through here.
      The narrowest navigable channel inside the strait is about 39 kilometres
      across — a third the width of Lake Washington seen end to end.
      Big tankers don't have a third of that to manoeuvre in: the
      international Traffic Separation Scheme gives outbound and inbound traffic
      a single 3-kilometre lane each, with a buffer between.
    </p>
    <p>
      What that geometry means is that <em>a small country with a long
      coastline on the right side</em> can interrupt one of the planet's
      biggest economic arteries with relatively little. Iran's Bandar Abbas
      sits just inside the channel; the islands of Qeshm, Larak and Hormuz
      give it close-in vantage. The two seizures this week were both within
      visual range of those islands.
    </p>
    <p>
      Cartographically the choice I made on this map is the small one:
      I kept the view <em>flat and tight</em>. Newsroom maps of the same week
      reach for a tilted satellite perspective; that style is good for the
      eye but bad for measuring. A flat top-down map lets a reader put a
      finger on the seizure pin and a finger on Khasab and see, without help,
      how short that distance really is.
    </p>
    <p class="aside">
      <em>A small disclosure.</em> The seizure pins are placed from open AIS
      reports and may shift as positions are corrected. The shipping-lane
      drawing follows the Traffic Separation Scheme but is sketched, not
      survey-grade.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div slot="notebook-zh">
    <p>
      全世界海上运输的原油，大部分都从这里过。海峡里可通航的最窄处约 39 公里宽——
      大约相当于华盛顿湖南北长度的三分之一。可大型油轮真正能动的水面远没有这么宽：
      国际航道分隔系统给进、出两个方向各划出 3 公里宽的单向航道，中间留一条缓冲。
    </p>
    <p>
      这条几何形状意味着：<em>一个海岸线正好长在'对的那一边'的小国</em>，
      只需要很有限的力量，就能切断地球上最重要的几条经济动脉之一。
      伊朗的阿巴斯港正好就坐在水道边，外加格什姆岛、拉腊克岛、霍尔木兹岛
      构成的近距离观察哨位。这周的两次扣船，都发生在这些岛屿的视野之内。
    </p>
    <p>
      在制图上我做的选择只有一个小决定：保持<em>正射、平面、贴近</em>。
      这一周新闻里那些图，多数喜欢用倾斜卫星视角——那种风格悦目，但不便于测量。
      一张正俯视的图，让读者一根手指按在扣船标记上、另一根按在哈萨布上，
      不用任何辅助就能看见——这两点之间的距离究竟有多近。
    </p>
    <p class="aside">
      <em>附注：</em>扣船标记按公开 AIS 报告放置，未来如有修订两侧同步更新。
      航道走向参照国际航道分隔系统，但为示意性绘制，并非测绘等级。
    </p>
  </div>

  <ul slot="provenance-en">
    <li>Coastline: <a href="https://www.naturalearthdata.com/downloads/10m-physical-vectors/" rel="noopener">Natural Earth 1:10m</a> via <code>world-atlas@2</code> (50m fallback).</li>
    <li>Strait baseline traffic: <a href="https://www.eia.gov/todayinenergy/detail.php?id=55339" rel="noopener">EIA, World Oil Transit Chokepoints</a> — about 18.5 million barrels a day, ≈20% of global seaborne oil.</li>
    <li>Channel width: International Hydrographic Organization charts; minimum navigable channel ≈ 21 nautical miles ≈ 39 km.</li>
    <li>Vessel-seizure positions (illustrative): open-source AIS reporting, 24–25 April 2026. Subject to revision.</li>
    <li>Source map &amp; build script: <code>src/pages/friday-harbor/2026-04-25-eye-of-the-needle.astro</code>.</li>
  </ul>

  <ul slot="provenance-zh">
    <li>海岸线：<a href="https://www.naturalearthdata.com/downloads/10m-physical-vectors/" rel="noopener">Natural Earth 1:10m</a>，经 <code>world-atlas@2</code>（fallback 至 50m）加载。</li>
    <li>海峡基线流量：<a href="https://www.eia.gov/todayinenergy/detail.php?id=55339" rel="noopener">EIA《世界石油海运咽喉点》</a>——约 1850 万桶 / 日，相当于全球海运原油的约 20%。</li>
    <li>水道宽度：国际海道测量组织海图；可通航最窄处约 21 海里 ≈ 39 公里。</li>
    <li>扣船坐标（示意）：开源 AIS 报告，2026 年 4 月 24–25 日。位置可能后续修订。</li>
    <li>源码与构建脚本：<code>src/pages/friday-harbor/2026-04-25-eye-of-the-needle.astro</code>。</li>
  </ul>
</FridayHarborLayout>

<style>
  .hormuz-figure { margin: 0; }
  .hormuz-stage {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;
    background: transparent;
    border: 0;
    border-radius: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
  }
  .hormuz-stage svg { display: block; width: 100%; height: 100%; }
  .map-status {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .hormuz-figure figcaption {
    margin: 1.1rem 0.2rem 0;
    font-size: 0.94rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-family: var(--serif);
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 880px;
  }
  .hormuz-figure figcaption b { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 500; }
  .hormuz-figure figcaption .event-mark { color: var(--rose); font-weight: 600; }
  .hormuz-figure figcaption em { color: var(--uw-purple-deep); font-style: italic; }
  .aside {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--rule);
    padding-left: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-size: 0.88rem !important;
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>

<script type="module">
  import * as d3 from 'https://esm.sh/d3@7';
  import { feature } from 'https://esm.sh/topojson-client@3';

  // Keep the map flat and tight: the story is about measurable constraint, not
  // scenic perspective.
  const STRAIT = [56.30, 26.55];
  const VIEW_WINDOW = {
    west: 55.52,
    east: 57.02,
    south: 25.90,
    north: 27.36
  };
  const STRAIT_CORRIDOR = [
    [55.64, 26.50],
    [56.18, 26.55],
    [56.92, 26.53]
  ];

  const SEIZURES = [
    { date: '2026-04-24', lon: 56.20, lat: 26.40, label: { en: 'M/V Ararat',     zh: '阿拉拉特号' } },
    { date: '2026-04-25', lon: 56.55, lat: 26.55, label: { en: 'M/V Heron Star', zh: '苍鹭星号' } }
  ];

  const CITIES = [
    { name: { en: 'Bandar Abbas',    zh: '阿巴斯港' }, lon: 56.27, lat: 27.18 },
    { name: { en: 'Qeshm',           zh: '格什姆'   }, lon: 56.27, lat: 26.95 },
    { name: { en: 'Khasab',          zh: '哈萨布'   }, lon: 56.25, lat: 26.21 }
  ];

  // Strait islands — small italic labels
  const ISLANDS = [
    { name: { en: 'Qeshm I.',   zh: '格什姆岛'   }, lon: 55.95, lat: 26.78 },
    { name: { en: 'Larak I.',   zh: '拉腊克岛'   }, lon: 56.38, lat: 26.85 },
    { name: { en: 'Hormuz I.',  zh: '霍尔木兹岛' }, lon: 56.47, lat: 27.07 }
  ];

  // Oil & gas terminals — small rose squares
  const TERMINALS = [
    { name: 'Bandar Abbas',  lon: 56.20, lat: 27.10 },   // Iran (mainland)
    { name: 'Hengam',        lon: 55.85, lat: 26.65 }    // Iran offshore island
  ];

  // (Annotation callouts removed — leader lines made the page noisy.
  //  All factual annotations live in the figcaption and notebook below.)

  const css = getComputedStyle(document.documentElement);
  const c = {
    paper:   css.getPropertyValue('--bg-card').trim()   || '#f5efe2',
    paper2:  css.getPropertyValue('--bg-deep').trim()   || '#ddd4c2',
    rule:    css.getPropertyValue('--rule').trim()      || '#d6cdbf',
    ink:     css.getPropertyValue('--ink').trim()       || '#2c2823',
    inkSoft: css.getPropertyValue('--ink-soft').trim()  || '#6c6358',
    inkFaint:css.getPropertyValue('--ink-faint').trim() || '#98907f',
    purple:  css.getPropertyValue('--uw-purple').trim() || '#6a5a6e',
    purpleD: css.getPropertyValue('--uw-purple-deep').trim() || '#4a3e4d',
    sage:    css.getPropertyValue('--sage').trim()      || '#8e9c8a',
    sageS:   css.getPropertyValue('--sage-soft').trim() || '#b4bdaf',
    rose:    css.getPropertyValue('--rose').trim()      || '#c2a094',
    mist:    css.getPropertyValue('--mist').trim()      || '#a8b1b3',
  };

  let _land = null;
  let _borders = null;

  const NE = 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/martynafford/natural-earth-geojson@master/10m';

  Promise.all([
    fetch(`${NE}/physical/ne_10m_land.json`).then(r => r.ok ? r.json() : Promise.reject()),
    fetch(`${NE}/cultural/ne_10m_admin_0_boundary_lines_land.json`).then(r => r.ok ? r.json() : Promise.reject()),
  ])
  .then(([landGJ, borderGJ]) => {
    _land    = landGJ;
    _borders = borderGJ;
    requestAnimationFrame(() => draw());
  })
  .catch(() => {
    // fallback: world-atlas 50m countries (less ideal — has admin breaks in fill)
    fetch('https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/world-atlas@2/countries-50m.json')
      .then(r => r.json())
      .then(w => {
        _land = feature(w, w.objects.countries);
        _borders = null;
        requestAnimationFrame(() => draw());
      });
  });

  window.addEventListener('resize', () => { if (_land) draw(); });

  const fhRoot = document.querySelector('.fh-root');
  if (fhRoot) {
    new MutationObserver(() => { if (_land) draw(); })
      .observe(fhRoot, { attributes: true, attributeFilter: ['data-lang'] });
  }

  function currentLang() {
    return fhRoot && fhRoot.getAttribute('data-lang') === 'zh' ? 'zh' : 'en';
  }

  function draw() {
    const land = _land;
    const borders = _borders;
    if (!land) return;
    const stage = document.getElementById('stage');
    if (!stage) return;

    const W = stage.clientWidth | 0;
    const H = stage.clientHeight | 0;
    if (W < 50 || H < 50) { requestAnimationFrame(() => draw()); return; }

    stage.innerHTML = '';
    const svg = d3.select(stage).append('svg')
      .attr('viewBox', `0 0 ${W} ${H}`)
      .attr('width', W).attr('height', H)
      .style('display', 'block')
      .style('overflow', 'hidden');
    const lang = currentLang();

    const padL = 2, padR = 2, padT = 2, padB = 28;
    const mapW = W - padL - padR;
    const mapH = H - padT - padB;
    if (mapW < 50 || mapH < 50) return;

    const mercatorY = lat => Math.log(Math.tan(Math.PI / 4 + lat * Math.PI / 360));
    const lonSpan = (VIEW_WINDOW.east - VIEW_WINDOW.west) * Math.PI / 180;
    const ySpan = mercatorY(VIEW_WINDOW.north) - mercatorY(VIEW_WINDOW.south);
    const scale = Math.min(mapW / lonSpan, mapH / ySpan) * 0.98;
    const centerLon = (VIEW_WINDOW.west + VIEW_WINDOW.east) / 2;
    const centerLat = (VIEW_WINDOW.south + VIEW_WINDOW.north) / 2;
    const projection = d3.geoMercator()
      .center([centerLon, centerLat])
      .scale(scale)
      .translate([padL + mapW / 2, padT + mapH / 2])
      .clipExtent([[padL, padT], [padL + mapW, padT + mapH]])
      .precision(0.1);
    const path = d3.geoPath(projection);

    // Site-native palette: paper, putty, sage, rose, and dusty purple.
    const SEA       = c.mist;
    const SHOAL     = c.sageS;
    const LAND      = c.paper;
    const COAST_DK  = c.inkSoft;
    const COAST_LT  = 'rgba(108,99,88,0.28)';
    const ROUTE     = 'rgba(245,239,226,0.92)';
    const ROUTE_DIM = 'rgba(245,239,226,0.62)';
    const FOCUS     = c.purpleD;

    function addText(g, text, x, y, attrs = {}) {
      const halo = g.append('text')
        .attr('x', x).attr('y', y)
        .attr('stroke', attrs.halo || 'rgba(245,239,226,0.86)')
        .attr('stroke-width', attrs.haloWidth || 3.5)
        .attr('stroke-linejoin', 'round')
        .attr('paint-order', 'stroke')
        .attr('fill', attrs.fill || c.ink)
        .attr('font-family', attrs.fontFamily || 'Inter, "Noto Sans CJK", sans-serif')
        .attr('font-size', attrs.fontSize || 10.5)
        .attr('font-weight', attrs.fontWeight || 500)
        .attr('font-style', attrs.fontStyle || 'normal')
        .attr('letter-spacing', attrs.letterSpacing || 0)
        .attr('text-anchor', attrs.anchor || 'middle')
        .text(text);
      return halo;
    }

    const clipId = 'fh-mapclip';
    const defs = svg.append('defs');
    defs.append('clipPath').attr('id', clipId)
      .append('rect').attr('x', padL).attr('y', padT).attr('width', mapW).attr('height', mapH);

    svg.append('rect').attr('x', padL).attr('y', padT)
      .attr('width', mapW).attr('height', mapH).attr('fill', c.paper2);

    // All geography clipped to the map area
    const mapG = svg.append('g').attr('clip-path', `url(#${clipId})`);

    // SEA — solid muted blue. A flat rectangle keeps the reader in measuring mode.
    mapG.append('rect').attr('x', padL).attr('y', padT)
      .attr('width', mapW).attr('height', mapH)
      .attr('fill', SEA)
      .attr('stroke', 'none');

    // Subtle graticule: map ticks, not decoration.
    mapG.append('g').selectAll('path').data(d3.geoGraticule().step([0.5, 0.5]).lines())
      .join('path').attr('d', path).attr('fill', 'none')
      .attr('stroke', c.rule).attr('stroke-opacity', 0.22).attr('stroke-width', 0.4);

    // BATHYMETRY: a wider pale-blue stroke under the land creates a halo of
    // shallow water around all coast — without any filter (those failed earlier
    // because the source path is world-scale).
    mapG.append('path').datum(land).attr('d', path)
      .attr('fill', 'none')
      .attr('stroke', SHOAL)
      .attr('stroke-width', 8)
      .attr('stroke-opacity', 0.55);
    // A second narrower band, slightly darker, gives the halo two-step gradation
    mapG.append('path').datum(land).attr('d', path)
      .attr('fill', 'none')
      .attr('stroke', c.sage)
      .attr('stroke-width', 2.2)
      .attr('stroke-opacity', 0.32);

    // LAND fill — drawn AFTER the halo so the halo only shows outside the coast
    mapG.append('path').datum(land).attr('d', path)
      .attr('fill', LAND)
      .attr('stroke', COAST_LT)
      .attr('stroke-width', 1.8)
      .attr('stroke-linejoin', 'round');

    // Crisp dark coastline on top
    mapG.append('path').datum(land).attr('d', path)
      .attr('fill', 'none')
      .attr('stroke', COAST_DK)
      .attr('stroke-width', 0.8)
      .attr('stroke-linejoin', 'round')
      .attr('stroke-linecap', 'round');

    // Country borders
    if (borders) {
      mapG.append('path').datum(borders).attr('d', path)
        .attr('fill', 'none')
        .attr('stroke', 'rgba(108,99,88,0.42)')
        .attr('stroke-width', 0.45)
        .attr('stroke-dasharray', '3 2');
    }

    const projectedLine = d3.line()
      .curve(d3.curveCatmullRom.alpha(0.5))
      .x(d => d[0])
      .y(d => d[1]);
    mapG.append('path')
      .attr('d', projectedLine(STRAIT_CORRIDOR.map(point => projection(point)).filter(Boolean)))
      .attr('fill', 'none')
      .attr('stroke', ROUTE_DIM)
      .attr('stroke-width', 10)
      .attr('stroke-linecap', 'round')
      .attr('opacity', 0.34);
    mapG.append('path')
      .attr('d', projectedLine(STRAIT_CORRIDOR.map(point => projection(point)).filter(Boolean)))
      .attr('fill', 'none')
      .attr('stroke', ROUTE)
      .attr('stroke-width', 1.8)
      .attr('stroke-linecap', 'round')
      .attr('stroke-dasharray', '7 6')
      .attr('opacity', 0.88);

    const notePoint = projection([56.64, 26.34]);
    if (notePoint) {
      addText(mapG, lang === 'zh' ? '可通航最窄处约 39 公里' : 'narrowest navigable reach approx. 39 km', notePoint[0], notePoint[1], {
        fill: FOCUS,
        fontSize: lang === 'zh' ? 10.5 : 10,
        fontWeight: 650,
        anchor: 'middle',
        haloWidth: 4
      });
    }

    // Sea labels — water bodies named so the reader is oriented
    const seaSerif = lang === 'zh'
      ? '"Noto Serif SC", "Songti SC", "STSong", serif'
      : '"Cormorant Garamond", Georgia, serif';
    const seaLabels = lang === 'zh'
      ? [ { t: '波斯湾',         lon: 55.68, lat: 26.95, size: 16, weight: 500, sp: '0.18em' },
          { t: '阿曼湾',         lon: 56.72, lat: 25.96, size: 16, weight: 500, sp: '0.18em' },
          { t: '霍尔木兹海峡',   lon: 56.50, lat: 26.55, size: 12, weight: 400, sp: '0.30em', italic: true } ]
      : [ { t: 'Persian Gulf',     lon: 55.68, lat: 26.95, size: 14, weight: 500, sp: '0.18em', italic: true },
          { t: 'Gulf of Oman',     lon: 56.72, lat: 25.96, size: 14, weight: 500, sp: '0.18em', italic: true },
          { t: 'Strait of Hormuz', lon: 56.50, lat: 26.55, size: 11, weight: 400, sp: '0.30em', italic: true } ];
    svg.append('g').selectAll('text').data(seaLabels).join('text')
      .each(function (d) {
        const p = projection([d.lon, d.lat]);
        if (!p) { d3.select(this).remove(); return; }
        addText(d3.select(this.parentNode), d.t, p[0], p[1], {
          fill: c.purpleD,
          fontFamily: seaSerif,
          fontStyle: d.italic ? 'italic' : 'normal',
          fontWeight: d.weight || 400,
          fontSize: d.size,
          letterSpacing: d.sp || '0.08em',
          halo: 'rgba(168,177,179,0.48)',
          haloWidth: 3
        });
        d3.select(this).remove();
      });

    // Island labels — small italic, ink-soft
    const islandSerif = seaSerif;
    svg.append('g').selectAll('text').data(ISLANDS).join('text')
      .each(function (d) {
        const p = projection([d.lon, d.lat]);
        if (!p) { d3.select(this).remove(); return; }
        addText(d3.select(this.parentNode), d.name[lang], p[0], p[1] - 6, {
          fill: c.inkSoft,
          fontFamily: islandSerif,
          fontStyle: 'italic',
          fontSize: 9.5,
          letterSpacing: '0.04em',
          haloWidth: 3
        });
        d3.select(this).remove();
      });

    // Oil & gas terminals — rose squares
    mapG.append('g').selectAll('rect').data(TERMINALS).join('rect')
      .each(function (d) {
        const p = projection([d.lon, d.lat]);
        if (!p) return;
        d3.select(this).attr('x', p[0] - 3.5).attr('y', p[1] - 3.5)
          .attr('width', 7).attr('height', 7)
          .attr('fill', c.rose).attr('stroke', c.paper).attr('stroke-width', 1);
      });

    // Country labels — small, restrained
    const countryLabels = lang === 'zh'
      ? [ { t: '伊朗',  lon: 56.05, lat: 27.18, size: 14 },
          { t: '阿曼',  lon: 56.43, lat: 26.02, size: 12 },
          { t: '阿联酋', lon: 55.82, lat: 25.95, size: 10 } ]
      : [ { t: 'IRAN',  lon: 56.05, lat: 27.18, size: 14 },
          { t: 'OMAN',  lon: 56.43, lat: 26.02, size: 11 },
          { t: 'U.A.E.', lon: 55.82, lat: 25.95, size: 10 } ];
    const countrySerif = lang === 'zh'
      ? '"Noto Serif SC", "Songti SC", "STSong", serif'
      : '"Cormorant Garamond", Georgia, serif';
    svg.append('g').selectAll('text').data(countryLabels).join('text')
      .each(function (d) {
        const p = projection([d.lon, d.lat]);
        if (!p) { d3.select(this).remove(); return; }
        addText(d3.select(this.parentNode), d.t, p[0], p[1], {
          fill: c.purpleD,
          fontFamily: countrySerif,
          fontStyle: lang === 'zh' ? 'normal' : 'italic',
          fontWeight: 500,
          fontSize: d.size || 14,
          letterSpacing: lang === 'zh' ? '0.18em' : '0.16em',
          haloWidth: 4
        });
        d3.select(this).remove();
      });

    // City dots (small, dark)
    svg.append('g').selectAll('g').data(CITIES).join('g')
      .each(function (d) {
        const p = projection([d.lon, d.lat]);
        if (!p) { d3.select(this).remove(); return; }
        const g = d3.select(this).attr('transform', `translate(${p[0]},${p[1]})`);
        g.append('circle').attr('r', 2.4).attr('fill', c.ink)
          .attr('stroke', c.paper).attr('stroke-width', 1.2);
        addText(g, d.name[lang], 6, 3, {
          fill: c.ink,
          fontSize: 10,
          fontWeight: 600,
          anchor: 'start',
          haloWidth: 3
        });
      });

    // Seizure pins — numbered (① ②). Names live in the figcaption now.
    const numerals = ['①', '②', '③', '④', '⑤'];
    svg.append('g').selectAll('g').data(SEIZURES).join('g')
      .each(function (d, i) {
        const p = projection([d.lon, d.lat]);
        if (!p) { d3.select(this).remove(); return; }
        const g = d3.select(this).attr('transform', `translate(${p[0]},${p[1]})`);
        // outer attention ring
        g.append('circle').attr('r', 16).attr('fill', 'none')
          .attr('stroke', c.rose).attr('stroke-opacity', 0.52).attr('stroke-width', 1.3);
        const halo = g.append('circle').attr('r', 9).attr('fill', c.rose).attr('fill-opacity', 0.34)
          .attr('stroke', c.rose).attr('stroke-width', 1);
        halo.append('animate')
          .attr('attributeName', 'r')
          .attr('values', '7;12;7')
          .attr('dur', '2.8s')
          .attr('repeatCount', 'indefinite');
        halo.append('animate')
          .attr('attributeName', 'fill-opacity')
          .attr('values', '0.36;0.16;0.36')
          .attr('dur', '2.8s')
          .attr('repeatCount', 'indefinite');
        g.append('circle').attr('r', 4.5).attr('fill', c.rose)
          .attr('stroke', c.purpleD).attr('stroke-width', 1);
        // numeral, slightly NE of the pin
        g.append('text').attr('x', 13).attr('y', -10)
          .attr('fill', c.purpleD).attr('font-size', 16).attr('font-weight', 700)
          .attr('font-family', 'Inter, "Noto Sans CJK", sans-serif')
          .attr('paint-order', 'stroke')
          .attr('stroke', 'rgba(245,239,226,0.9)')
          .attr('stroke-width', 3)
          .attr('stroke-linejoin', 'round')
          .text(numerals[i] || (i + 1));
      });

    // Scale bar — pinned to bottom-left of map area, with 0 / 25 / 50 ticks
    const refLat = STRAIT[1];
    const totalKm = 50;
    const halfKm  = 25;
    const degLonTotal = totalKm / (111 * Math.cos(refLat * Math.PI / 180));
    const degLonHalf  = halfKm  / (111 * Math.cos(refLat * Math.PI / 180));
    const ra = projection([STRAIT[0], refLat]);
    const rb = projection([STRAIT[0] + degLonTotal, refLat]);
    const rh = projection([STRAIT[0] + degLonHalf,  refLat]);
    if (ra && rb && rh) {
      const barPx  = Math.abs(rb[0] - ra[0]);
      const halfPx = Math.abs(rh[0] - ra[0]);
      const x0 = padL + 22;
      const y0 = padT + mapH - 28;
      const sg = svg.append('g').attr('transform', `translate(${x0}, ${y0})`);
      // bar
      sg.append('line').attr('x2', barPx).attr('stroke', c.inkSoft).attr('stroke-width', 1.1);
      // ticks
      [0, halfPx, barPx].forEach(x => {
        sg.append('line').attr('x1', x).attr('x2', x).attr('y1', -4).attr('y2', 4)
          .attr('stroke', c.inkSoft).attr('stroke-width', 1.1);
      });
      // labels
      sg.append('text').attr('x', 0).attr('y', -7).attr('text-anchor', 'middle')
        .attr('fill', c.inkSoft).attr('font-size', 9).attr('font-family', 'Inter, sans-serif').text('0');
      sg.append('text').attr('x', halfPx).attr('y', -7).attr('text-anchor', 'middle')
        .attr('fill', c.inkSoft).attr('font-size', 9).attr('font-family', 'Inter, sans-serif').text('25');
      sg.append('text').attr('x', barPx).attr('y', -7).attr('text-anchor', 'middle')
        .attr('fill', c.inkSoft).attr('font-size', 9).attr('font-family', 'Inter, sans-serif').text(`${totalKm} km`);
    }

    // No north arrow: at this scale the coastlines and labels orient the reader.
  }

  // (lang re-render is wired up at the top, with a cached `_land`.)
</script>
